---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Game Engine Comparison 2026: Unity vs Unreal vs Godot",
  "description": "Feature-by-feature comparison of top game engines including pricing, platform support, languages, community size, and notable games.",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "leeroyjenkins.quest"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "GAB Ventures",
    "url": "https://gab.ae"
  }
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="leeroyjenkins"
  title="Game Engine Comparison 2026: Unity vs Unreal vs Godot"
  description="Feature-by-feature comparison of top game engines including pricing, platform support, languages, community size, and notable games."
  canonical="https://leeroyjenkins.quest/game-engine-comparison" schema={schema}
>
  <style>
:root {
            --bg-base: #0a0b10;
            --bg-card: #111318;
            --border: #1e2030;
            --accent: #9333EA;
            --text-primary: #d8d0e8;
            --text-secondary: #888;
            --font-ui: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
            --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        }

        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: var(--font-ui);
            background: var(--bg-base);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 40px 24px;
        }

        /* Hero */
        .hero {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 60px 0;
            position: relative;
        }

        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 3rem;
            font-weight: 900;
            letter-spacing: -1.5px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
            -webkit-background-clip: text;
            -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        }

        .hero p {
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        /* Cards */
        .stats-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
            gap: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 60px;
        }

        .stat-card {
            background: var(--bg-card);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 12px;
            padding: 24px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .stat-card h3 {
            font-size: 1rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .stat-card .value {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            color: var(--accent);
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
        }

        /* Interactive Data Table */
        .table-controls {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 16px;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
            background: var(--bg-card);
            padding: 16px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        .search-input {
            background: var(--bg-base);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            padding: 10px 16px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-family: var(--font-ui);
            flex-grow: 1;
            max-width: 300px;
        }

        .search-input:focus {
            outline: none;
            border-color: var(--accent);
        }

        .filter-select {
            background: var(--bg-base);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            padding: 10px 16px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-family: var(--font-ui);
        }

        .table-container {
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin-bottom: 60px;
            background: var(--bg-card);
            border-radius: 12px;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            text-align: left;
        }

        th, td {
            padding: 16px 20px;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }

        th {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            cursor: pointer;
            user-select: none;
        }

        th:hover {
            color: var(--text-primary);
        }

        th.sort-asc::after { content: " ↑"; }
        th.sort-desc::after { content: " ↓"; }

        tr:last-child td {
            border-bottom: none;
        }

        tr:hover td {
            background: rgba(147, 51, 234, 0.05);
        }

        .engine-name {
            font-weight: 700;
            color: #fff;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
        }

        .font-mono {
            font-family: var(--font-mono);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        .badge {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            background: rgba(147, 51, 234, 0.1);
            color: var(--accent);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin-right: 4px;
            margin-bottom: 4px;
        }

        /* FAQ Section */
        .section-title {
            font-size: 2rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            margin-bottom: 24px;
            color: #fff;
        }

        .faq-list {
            display: grid;
            gap: 16px;
            margin-bottom: 60px;
        }

        .faq-item {
            background: var(--bg-card);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 24px;
        }

        .faq-item h3 {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
            color: #fff;
        }

        .faq-item p {
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }

        /* Methodology */
        .methodology {
            background: var(--bg-card);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 8px;
            padding: 32px;
            margin-bottom: 60px;
        }

        .methodology h2 {
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        .methodology p {
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }

        /* Footer */
        .footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 40px 24px;
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            font-size: 0.85rem;
        }

        .footer a {
            color: var(--accent);
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .footer a:hover {
            text-decoration: underline;
        }

        .copy-btn {
            background: transparent;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            padding: 4px 8px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            transition: all 0.2s;
            margin-top: 8px;
        }

        .copy-btn:hover {
            border-color: var(--accent);
            color: var(--accent);
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
            th, td { padding: 12px; }
            .table-controls { flex-direction: column; align-items: stretch; }
            .search-input { max-width: none; }
        }
  </style>

<div class="container">
    <div class="hero">
        <h1>Game Engine Comparison 2026</h1>
        <p>A feature-by-feature comparison of top game engines including pricing, platform support, languages, community size, and notable games. Find the right engine for your next project.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Stats Section (Populated via JS) -->
    <div class="stats-grid" id="stats-grid">
        <!-- Template injected by JS -->
    </div>

    <!-- Interactive Data Table -->
    <h2 class="section-title">Engine Comparison</h2>
    <div class="table-controls">
        <input type="text" id="searchInput" class="search-input" placeholder="Search engines, languages, platforms...">
        <select id="filterSelect" class="filter-select">
            <option value="all">All Licenses</option>
            <option value="Proprietary">Proprietary</option>
            <option value="MIT">MIT / Open Source</option>
            <option value="Defold License">Defold License</option>
        </select>
        <button id="resetSortBtn" class="copy-btn">Reset Sort</button>
    </div>

    <div class="table-container">
        <table id="engineTable">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th data-sort="engine">Engine</th>
                    <th data-sort="license">License</th>
                    <th data-sort="pricingModel">Pricing</th>
                    <th data-sort="languages">Languages</th>
                    <th data-sort="platforms">Platforms</th>
                    <th data-sort="githubStars">GitHub Stars</th>
                    <th data-sort="steamGames">Steam Games</th>
                    <th data-sort="itchGames">itch.io Games</th>
                    <th data-sort="notableGames">Notable Games</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody id="tableBody">
                <!-- Data injected by JS -->
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Which game engine is best for beginners?</h3>
            <p>Godot and Construct 3 are often recommended for beginners. Godot's node-based architecture and Python-like GDScript make it easy to learn. Construct 3 offers visual scripting, eliminating the need to write traditional code while teaching core logic concepts.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>What is the difference between Unity and Unreal Engine?</h3>
            <p>Unity uses C# and is highly versatile for 2D, 3D, and mobile development, boasting a massive asset store. Unreal Engine uses C++ and Blueprints (visual scripting), excelling in high-fidelity 3D graphics and large-scale PC/Console games right out of the box.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Are open-source game engines viable for commercial games?</h3>
            <p>Absolutely. Godot (MIT License) has been used for highly successful commercial games like Sonic Colors: Ultimate and Brotato. Open-source engines mean you own your tools, avoid royalty fees, and can modify the engine source code if needed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>How do game engine royalties work?</h3>
            <p>Proprietary engines often charge based on revenue. For example, Unreal Engine charges a 5% royalty only after a game grosses $1 million USD. Unity recently updated its model to include revenue thresholds and per-seat licensing depending on the tier. Always read the latest EULA.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
            <h3>Which engine is best for 2D games?</h3>
            <p>GameMaker and Godot are industry favorites for 2D. GameMaker powers hits like Undertale and Hotline Miami with its specialized 2D workflow. Godot features a dedicated 2D rendering engine (unlike engines that fake 2D in a 3D space), making it extremely efficient.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Methodology -->
    <div class="methodology">
        <h2>Methodology</h2>
        <p>This study collects data on 10 prominent game engines. Data was gathered from official engine websites, GitHub API (for open-source repositories), Steam search results, and itch.io tags.</p>
        <p>Metrics like Steam and itch.io game counts are estimates based on platform search results and user-applied tags. Null values indicate data that was unavailable or inapplicable at the time of collection.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Footer -->


